msIdentifier.repository: Library at the Herbert D. Katz Center for Advanced Judaic Studies

msContents.summary: Text of the Pentateuch and haftarot; begins with Bereshit XI, 4; concludes with Isaiah 40:13 (hafṭarat ʻEḳev); accompanied by Masorah. A few pages at the end of Ṿa-yiḳra and at the beginning of Devarim seem to be missing and replaced by pages from a printed book.

respStmt.name: Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning

supportDesc.extent: 213 leaves : 250 x 200 (145 x 125) mm bound to 265 x 220 mm

collation.p: Parchment, ii (20th-century) + 213 + ii (20th-century); 1-5⁸ 6⁸(-1) 7-16⁸ 17⁶ 18¹² 19⁸ 20⁴ 21-27⁸; [1-131, 133-214], modern foliation in pencil, upper left recto. Catchwords on the last leaf of many gatherings, lower left verso.

origin.p: Written in Western Europe in the 14th or 15th century?

history.provenance: Formerly held in the Library of Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning; given to Dropsie College by David Werner Amram in 1924.
